\begin_layout Subsubsection
Calipers
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One of the oldest ways to accurately measure distances is with a pair of
 calipers.
 Calipers come in many variants, but all have the same basic concept--to
 place the tips of the caliper on either side of the feature being measured,
 and display the distance on a dial, slider, or digital scale.
 Older calipers had no readout and required the user to hold the tips against
 a scale to find the distance.
